<<<<<<< HEAD

======= The SBOL data model's Library for RDF and Json. The objects of this type represent an organizational container which helps users and developers conceptualize a set of DNA components and SequenceFeatures as a group. Any combination of these objects can be added to a library, annotated with a displayID, name and description and be shared on the web. Such collections could be a set of restriction enzyme recognition sites, such as the features commonly used for BBF RFC 10 BioBricks. A library could contain all the DNA components used in a specific project, lab, or any custom grouping specified by the user. COMMENT: Mike Galdzicki thinks Library is not necessary as generic metadata element, sets should be left to the lower level implementation (eg Collection in Java). Or be defined by queries, when there is information that groups the collection. And new objects should be created and named when the groupings are generally useful. Having a custom legacy objects for groups will cause downstream development issues as extensions for useful computable objects are proposed.
